@startuml network-scenario-1-hotspot
!include _standard-style.puml

title **Scenario 1 — Mobile Hotspot (Phone G5/LTE, no VPN)**

left to right direction

node "MacBook" as MB {
  [detect-network.sh] as DET
  [Proxydetox\n:3128] as PD
  [Claude CLI] as CLI
}

database "Phone Hotspot\n(NAT, public IP\nvia carrier)" as HS

cloud "Internet" as INET {
  [api.github.com] as GH
  [api.anthropic.com] as AN
}

rectangle "muc.proxy-pac.\nbmwgroup.net" as PAC #FFCDD2

' Flow
DET -[#red]-> PAC : 1. DNS lookup\n**NXDOMAIN**\n(no corp DNS)
DET -[#green,bold]-> HS : 2. curl --noproxy '*'\n(test direct)
HS -[#green,bold]-> GH : direct TCP/TLS ✓

DET .[#gray,dashed].> PD : 3. if direct FAILS:\nset https_proxy=:3128
PD .[#gray,dashed].> HS : DIRECT fallback\n(PAC unreachable)

CLI -[#green,bold]-> HS : 4. OAuth + API
HS -[#green,bold]-> AN : ✓ reachable

note bottom of MB
  **INSIDE_CN = false** (no corporate DNS)
  **Detection logic:**
  • Try direct curl → usually works on hotspot
  • If cellular DNS is slow (>3s timeout) → fallback:
    keep Proxydetox as proxy, it uses DIRECT mode
  **Result: Claude works ✓**
end note

@enduml
